.START 

Richard W. Taylor was elected vice president, corporate development, succeeding Walter B. LaBerge, who retired.
Mr. Taylor was president of the company's Information Systems Group, which is being phased out as part of a restructuring.
E. Allen Thompson, acting vice president, operations, was elected vice president, operations, for this military aerospace and electronics concern.
He succeeds Dale H. Daniels, who was named executive vice president, Lockheed Aeronautical Systems Co., a Burbank, Calif., unit. 

